Came here based on rave reviews on an expensive surge uber ride from Miami Beach and left thoroughly disappointed.  This is the first time google reviews and wynwood have disappointed me.  The place was not crowded on Saturday around 8:30pm - should have been a clue - and they did not have a working bathroom - don’t people want to wash hands before eating tacos with their hands??!!  But whatever, I stayed strong and waited for our order since I came here mainly to eat supposedly amazing tacos, right?  Our order of 2 lechons ($5 each, a decent amount of dry stringy pork on a cold tortilla), 1 steak ($8 each, good but not enough of the steak on a cold tortilla), and 1 octopus ($8 each, cold octopus on a cold tortilla) was not only disappointing in terms of quality but also quantity.  They definitely did not taste fresh nor authentic and we both left hungry and unsatisfied.  Miami must not have good tacos.  I can find better tacos in NYC for cheaper even in Manhattan not just in the outer boroughs and didn’t need these when I am on vacation in Miami.  Again, I’m no expert on tacos but this experience made me want to go eat tacos in LA - life is too short for these tacos.  I’m sorry for this scathing review but I need to be honest.  These are not worthy of 4.5 stars.

4.5 stars. A colleague and I visited Caja Caliente for lunch on a weekday. It's essentially a Cuban-inspired taco food truck with infrastructure built around it, creating a large covered outdoor dining area with plenty of seating and areas to relax. The vibe is a mix of Cuban, Caribbean, and hippy, and it blends well. I started with the blue crab croquettes, which were nostalgic for me as I grew up eating them. They were not the best I've ever had but were very good and enjoyable with a squirt of lime, hot sauce, and dipped in their cilantro-garlic sauce. I had the taco special which were two tacos for $6 with your choice of Cuban style pork or chicken. I went with the pork and they came fully loaded with the usual toppings. The tacos were tasty and the pork flavorful. Service was attentive and friendly. Overall, a great value for a no frills lunch for two at $20. I will definitely return and recommend to others.

Wow - absolutely floored. We were visiting and went fishing and found this place on a whim - man were we glad we did! Being from out of town and being a picky restaurant guy, I was skeptical when we saw it and it was kind of empty but then the scents of the food started hitting us and WOAH. Amazing smelling food was getting made and our mouths literally watered.  Once we actually got our food it didnt last long - everything was super fresh and all the flavors just meshed together for one of the best steak tacos followed by one of the best pulled pork tacos I have ever had in my life.

LISTEN, whoever can relate tacos to only Mexican food has NOT tried this place and honestly they're MISSING OUT! Yes I'm screaming because this place is amazinggggg! Funny thing is was hubby and I stumbled across this place by accident due to their beautifully colored decor! (If you read some of my reviews, you know my love for art & color!) and let me tell you, it's beyond amazing! They're Cuban tacos & they have so muchhhh flavor it'll leave your tastebuds speechless! And where else can you get croquetas, empanadas & tacos?! Don't worry, I'll wait!  We opted to try all kinds of things and I'm honestly surprised I didn't order 1 of everything on the menu, but don't fret, I will be back to finish off my tastings soon! lol We had the lechon taco, chicken taco, vacations frita taco, shrimp empanada & crab croqueta. EVERYTHING was phenomenal. Every+Single+Thing. The shrimp empanada tasted like shrimp enchilado in an empanada and I was ALL for it! The tacos were scrumptious with their sauces! The croqueta oh my god, I'm not even a crab fan UNTIL NOW! lol Great Great Great and I cannot describe how great it is! (Yes I will repeat the word great until you get it! lol) Had of course the Cuban classic sodas like Ironbeer cuz why not?! and everything was just amazing! Think of it like Mexican food made with Cuban parts!  The ambiance is amazing, it's a food truck with beautiful outdoor seating and decor! Everything is so colorful and mismatched yet coordinated all at the same time! The staff is AMAZING and so helpful, you'll feel like family! I enjoyed every bit of my experience here! Yes it is outdoors but there are fans and I didn't feel extra hot or anything. Although with the amazing food, I doubt you'll even notice.  This is a MUST try on your food list! Be there or be square!

By the time you told me the food was ready they had promised me the food 3 times before so I would have been happy with the refund but you were the one telling me that you were giving me the food anyway and the refund so I considered less rude to not even try it. If you go through my reviews I rarely give a bad review but 1 hour and everyone else with their orders when they arrived after me is pretty upsetting.
